The paper deals with mapping and self-localization in unknown environments, which are fundamental capabilities in robotics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel nonparametric pose graph that models data association and SLAM in a single framework, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also introduces an algorithm to alternate between inferring data association and performing SLAM, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.SY.
